==Devanagari script==
=== Hindi ===
'''ष'''

==== Pronunciation ====
/ ʂ /, pronounced alone it is / ʂə /, similar to the English ship, but with [[retroflex]] articulation.

====Consonant====

The second [[sibilant]] of the [[Devanagari]] script. Linguistically it is considered a retroflex [[w:Voiceless postalveolar fricative|voiceless postalveolar sibilant]].

=== Transliteration ===
*[[w:IAST|IAST]]: ṣ  Ṣ
*[[w:ITRANS|ITRANS]]: Sh

